    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gardens that employ one or more raised flat sections, either planted, paved, or gravelled, to allow efficient gardening on a sloping surface, to provide prospect overlooks, or for other reasons.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000045334/Boisset, Vertical Gardening (1988)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000094721/Loudon, An Encyclopaedia of Gardening (1825)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tuinen met een of meer verhoogde platte gedeelten, die beplant, geplaveid of met grind bedekt zijn, zodat efficiënt kan worden getuinierd op een helling. Ze kunnen aangelegd zijn om mooie uitzichten te bieden, of om andere redenen.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Jardins que empregam uma ou mais seções planas elevadas, plantadas, pavimentadas ou com cascalho, para permitir uma jardinagem eficiente em uma superfície inclinada, para fornecer vistas panorâmicas. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
